 and age|1941|10|13}}\n| birth_place      = [[Istanbul]]\n| death_date       = \n| death_place      = \n| resting_place    = \n| occupation       = Author, Academic, Social Scientist\n| language         = [[Turkish language|Turkish]]\n| residence        = Istanbul\n| nationality      = Turkish\n| citizenship      = Turkish\n| education        =  \u015ei\u015fli Terakki High School\n| alma_mater       = {{ubl|[[Ankara University]] <small>([[Bachelor's degree|BA]] 1963)</small> |[[Michigan  University]] <small>([[Master of Social Work|MSW]] 1966)</small> [[Hacettepe University]] <small>([[Doctor of Philosophy|PhD]] 1969)</small>}}\n| home_town        = \n| period           = \n| genre            = <!-- or: | genres = -->\n| subject          = [[Social Science]]\n| movement         = \n| notableworks     = <!-- or: | notablework = -->\n| spouse           = {{marriage|Bilgi Kongar|1963||reason=}}\n| partner          = \n| children         = 3\n| relatives        = \n| awards           = \n| signature        = \n| signature_alt    = \n| years_active     = 1966\u2013\n| module           = \n| website          = {{URL|https://www.kongar.org/}}\n| portaldisp       = <!-- \"on\", \"yes\", \"true\", etc.; or omit -->\n}}\n'''Re\u015fit Emre Kongar''' (born 13 October 1941) is a Turkish [[social scientist]],<ref name=\"Title Sociologist\">{{cite news|first=|last=|authorlink=|author=|curly=|title=Sedat Simavi \u00d6d\u00fclleri'ne internet habercili\u011fi de dahil oldu|url=https://www.ntv.com.tr/turkiye/sedat-simavi-odullerine-internet-haberciligi-de-dahil-oldu,YoicT2AboUK5s5N3b5MK6A|format=|agency=|work=|publisher=[[NTV (Turkey)]]|location=|id=|pages=|page=|date=14 June 2019|accessdate=11 May 2020|language=Tr|archiveurl=http://archive.is/wip/HswfC|archivedate=11 May 2020|quote=}}</ref> [[academic]], [[author]], and [[columnist]].<ref name=\"Title Columnlist\">{{cite news|first=|last=|authorlink=|author=|curly=|title=% 100 Futbol'a \u00f6d\u00fcl|url=https://www.ntv.com.tr/spor/100-futbola-odul,8MZdnqLSQ0SkPyhzN77WGA|format=|agency=|work=|publisher=[[NTV (Turkey)]]|location=|id=|pages=|page=|date=7 January 2010|accessdate=11 May 2020|language=Tr|archiveurl=http://archive.is/wip/IL8Rz|archivedate=11 May 2020|quote=}}</ref> As of 2020, he regularly writes his column at [[Cumhuriyet]].<ref name=\"2020 Position\">{{cite news|first=|last=|authorlink=|author=|curly=|title=Emre Kongar - Cumhuriyet|url=https://www.cumhuriyet.com.tr/koseyazari/22/Emre_Kongar.html|format=|agency=|work=|publisher=[[Cumhuriyet]]|location=|id=|pages=|page=|date=|accessdate=11 May 2020|language=Tr|archiveurl=|archivedate=11 May 2020|quote=}}</ref>\n\n==Early life and education==\nEmre Kongar was born in 1941 in Istanbul, to \u0130hsan Kongar, a [[Phylosophy|phylosophy teacher]] at \u015ei\u015fli Terakki High School and [[Pertevniyal High School]] and Mesude Kongar, also a phylosophy teacher at \u015ei\u015fli Terakki High School and Zapyon High School.<ref name=\"Kongar Biography\">{{cite news|first=|last=|authorlink=|author=|curly=|title=Emre Kongar'\u0131n K\u0131sa Ya\u015fam \u00d6yk\u00fcs\u00fc|url=https://www.kongar.org/CVtrk.php|format=|agency=|work=|publisher=kongar.org|location=|id=|pages=|page=|date=|accessdate=29 April 2020|language=Tr|archiveurl=http://archive.is/wip/nkJDo|archivedate=29 April 2020|quote=}}</ref> Engin, his elder brother, died with Yal\u00e7\u0131n M., a mount climbing fellow, following an fatal accident happened at [[Demirkaz\u0131k Peak]], located in [[Toros Mountains]] on 8 September 1956.<ref name=\"Engin Kongar\">{{cite news|first=|last=|authorlink=|author=Avc\u0131, \u00dcmran|curly=|title=Emre Kongar'dan 60 y\u0131l \u00f6ncesinin hikayesi|url=https://www.haberturk.com/yasam/haber/1263900-emre-kongardan-60-yil-oncesinin-hikayesi|format=|agency=|work=|publisher=[[Habert\u00fcrk]]|location=|id=|pages=|page=|date=8 July 2016|accessdate=30 April 2020|language=Tr|archiveurl=http://archive.is/wip/naWRO|archivedate=30 April 2020|quote=}}</ref>\n\nHe received his bachelor degree of [[public finance]] at [[Faculty of Political Science, Ankara University]] of [[Ankara University]] in 1963 and later studied [[Master of Social Work]] at [[Michigan State University]] until 1966.<ref name=\"Kongar Biography\"/> \n\n==Career==\nIn 1968, Kongar founded Social Studies Academy at [[Hacettepe University]], Ankara.\n\nIn 1983, Kongar was one of the earliest academics to protest [[Council of Higher Education (Turkey)|Council of Higher Education of Turkey]], the post-[[1980 Turkish coup d'\u00e9tat|coup d'\u00e9tat]] formed high level education supervision board, based on his claim that [[\u0130hsan Do\u011framac\u0131]] to found and lead this board, who was also the founder of [[Bilkent University]], a [[private university]], would disrupt [[Public property|public property function]] of the state owned universities.<ref name=\"1983 YOK Protest\">{{cite news|first=|last=|authorlink=|author=|curly=|title=T\u00fcrk bas\u0131n\u0131ndan izlenimler: Prof. Dr. Emre Kongar (Re\u015fit Emre Kongar)|url=https://www.aydinlik.com.tr/turk-basinindan-izlenimler-prof-dr-emre-kongar-resit-emre-kongar-hayati-asilyazici-kose-yazilari-aralik-2018|format=|agency=|work=|publisher=[[Ayd\u0131nl\u0131k]]|location=|id=|pages=|page=|date=9 December 2018|accessdate=11 May 2020|language=Tr|archiveurl=http://archive.is/bETs44|archivedate=11 May 2020|quote=}}</ref>\n\nBetween 1996 and 2000, until his retirement of academic profession, he lectured at Hacettepe, [[Y\u0131ld\u0131z Technical University|Y\u0131ld\u0131z Teknik]] and [[Istanbul University|Istanbul Universities]].<ref name=\"Yesevi Biography\">{{cite news|first=|last=|authorlink=|author=|curly=|title=Kongar, Emre|url=http://teis.yesevi.edu.tr/madde-detay/kongar-emre|format=|agency=|work=|publisher=[[Ahmet Yesevi University]]|location=|id=|pages=|page=|date=|accessdate=11 May 2020|language=Tr|archiveurl=http://archive.is/wCP1t|archivedate=11 May 2020|quote=}}</ref>\n\nKongar supported the [[2017 March for Justice|March for Justice]] led by [[Republican People's Party (Turkey)|Republican People's Party]] and walked along [[Kemal K\u0131l\u0131\u00e7daro\u011flu]]  on 21 June 2017.<ref name=\"March for Justice\">{{cite news|first=|last=|authorlink=|author=|curly=|title=Tezcan: K\u0131l\u0131\u00e7daro\u011flu'na y\u00f6nelik ad\u0131mda g\u00f6k kubbeyi dar ederiz|url=https://www.ntv.com.tr/turkiye/tezcan-kilicdarogluna-yonelik-adimda-gok-kubbeyi-dar-ederiz,nq1xKa77y0GwLRApdpj-fA|format=|agency=|work=|publisher=[[NTV (Turkey)]]|location=|id=|pages=|page=|date=21 June 2017|accessdate=11 May 2020|language=Tr|archiveurl=http://archive.is/wip/YJRtI|archivedate=11 May 2020|quote=}}</ref>\n\nHis book \"\u0130stanbul: 1940\u2019lardan Bug\u00fcne Efsaneler An\u0131lar \u0130zlenimler\" was published by Remzi Kitapevi in 2019.<ref name=\"2019 Book\">{{cite news|first=|last=|authorlink=|author=|curly=|title=\nEmre Kongar anlatt\u0131: Ona en az \u00fc\u00e7 kez \u00e2\u015f\u0131k oldum|url=https://odatv4.com/ona-en-az-uc-kez-sik-oldum-05101914.html|format=|agency=|work=|publisher=[[OdaTV]]|location=|id=|pages=|page=|date=5 October 2019|accessdate=11 May 2020|language=Tr|archiveurl=http://archive.is/NJc9j|archivedate=11 May 2020|quote=}}</ref>\n\n==Bibliography==\n===Books===\nSource:<ref name=\"Kongar Books\">{{cite news|first=|last=|authorlink=|author=|curly=|title=Yay\u0131nlanm\u0131\u015f Kitaplar\u0131n Lisesi|url=https://www.kongar.org/kitaplar.php|format=|agency=|work=|publisher=kongar.org|location=|id=|pages=|page=|date=|accessdate=29 April 2020|language=Tr|archiveurl=http://archive.is/dYTx6|archivedate=29 April 2020|quote=}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- \n! Year\n! Original Title\n! Publishing House\n|-\n|1972\n|\u0130nsan\u0131 Y\u00f6nlendirme ve Sosyal Hizmetler\n|T\u00fcrk Sosyal Bilimler Derne\u011fi Yay\u0131nlar\u0131\n|-\n|1982\n|Cavit Orhan T\u00fctengil\n|T\u00fcrk Dil Kurumu Yay\u0131nlar\u0131\n|-\n|1984 \n|\u00dcniversite \